## Memento Decay Workflow

Triggers: "decay check", "what's stale", "memento decay", "audit aged decisions"

### What it does
Finds aged `[D]` artifacts (default >30 days) whose invalidation triggers may have fired. Scores decay from three signals: git-log keyword grep (commits grouped by hash, multi-keyword AND weighted higher), vault-state contradiction (newer artifact with ≥2 overlapping terms), and age past 90 days.

### How to invoke
```bash
python3 <path-to-memento-os>/skills/memento-decay/decay.py [vault_root] [--age 30] [--format json] [--no-git] [--all] [--stopwords <file>]
```

A per-vault stopword list at `<vault_root>/.memento-stopwords` is loaded automatically. Use it to suppress project-specific noise words.

### Agent flow
1. Run with `--format json`.
2. For each LIKELY STALE candidate, prompt user: "Mark `[D]#N` as superseded? (y/n/skip)".
3. On `y`: change the priority cell in `_context.md` to `superseded`. Update `Decisions/` file frontmatter if it exists.
4. On `n` / `skip`: leave artifact, optionally capture an `[I]` insight explaining why the trigger hasn't fired.
